# MySystem — personal Claude Code config
#
# Strategy: ignore everything, whitelist tracked items explicitly.
# External skills (gstack and anything it installs) are NOT whitelisted,
# so they are ignored by default — no maintenance when gstack evolves.
# When adding a user-owned skill, add two lines here (see "User-owned
# skills" section below).

*

# Root files — tracked
!.gitignore
!.gitattributes
!CLAUDE.md
!CHANGELOG.md
!README.md
!SETUP.md
!RTK.md
!VERSION
!settings.json
!setup.sh
!install.sh

# Structural directories (whitelisted to let git descend into them)
!skills/
!hooks/
!hooks/**

# User-owned skills — tracked. Add a new entry here when you create one.
# Format: two lines per skill (directory + recursive contents).
!skills/bugbot/
!skills/bugbot/**
!skills/documentation-lookup/
!skills/documentation-lookup/**
!skills/search-first/
!skills/search-first/**
!skills/slow-down/
!skills/slow-down/**
!skills/verify-test/
!skills/verify-test/**

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
*.swp
.vscode/
